mpings2 = 5/\u2013\n| date = 13 August 2019\n| source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/1970/1970320/1970320.html CricketArchive\n}}\n'''Muhammad Ahsan Ali Khan''' ({{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|\u0639\u0644\u06cc \u062e\u0627\u0646}}}}); is an American [[cricket]]er. He made his [[List A cricket|List A]] debut in January 2016, playing for the composite [[ICC Americas cricket team|ICC Americas]] team in the [[2015\u201316 Regional Super50]]. On debut against [[Jamaica national cricket team|Jamaica]], he took the wickets of [[Devon Thomas]] and [[Aldane Thomas]], finishing with 2/63 from ten overs.<ref>[http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/951657.html Nagico Super50, Group A: Jamaica v ICC Americas at St Augustine, Jan 9, 2016] \u2013 ESPNcricinfo. Retrieved 13 January 2016.</ref> Khan was the only member of the ICC Americas squad to have not previously played for his national team.<ref>Peter Della Penna (7 October 2015). [http://www.espncricinfo.com/usa/content/story/926905.html \"Taylor, Ghous picked in 15-man ICC Americas squad\"] \u2013 ESPNcricinfo. Retrieved 13 January 2016.</ref> In July 2016 he was one of eleven uncapped players to be named for a USA selection camp ahead of the [[2016 ICC World Cricket League Division Four]] tournament in October.<ref name=\"camp\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/usa/content/story/1033385.html |title=Eleven uncapped players picked for USA national camp |accessdate=July 7, 2016 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 June 2018, he was selected to play for the Winnipeg Hawks in the players' draft for the [[2018 Global T20 Canada|inaugural edition]] of the [[Global T20 Canada]] tournament.<ref name=\"Squads1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/cricket/global-t20-canada-complete-squads |title=Global T20 Canada: Complete Squads |work=SportsKeeda |accessdate=4 June 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Squads2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.crictracker.com/global-t20-canada-league-full-squads-announced/ |title=Global T20 Canada League \u2013 Full Squads announced |work=CricTracker |accessdate=4 June 2018}}</ref> In August 2018, he was named in the United States' squad for the [[2018\u201319 ICC World Twenty20 Americas Qualifier]] tournament in [[Morrisville, North Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usacricket.org/team-usa-men/team-usa-squad-selected-for-icc-world-t20-americas-qualifier/ |title=Team USA Squad Selected for ICC World T20 Americas\u2019 Qualifier |work=USA Cricket |accessdate=August 22, 2018}}</ref> In October 2018, he was named in the United States' squad for the [[2018 ICC World Cricket League Division Three]] tournament in Oman.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/25015081/hayden-walsh-jr-aaron-jones-usa-squad-wcl-division-three |title=Hayden Walsh Jr, Aaron Jones in USA squad for WCL Division Three |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=18 October 2018}}</ref> Later the same month, he was named in the squad for the [[Khulna Titans]] team, following the draft for the [[2018\u201319 Bangladesh Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tigercricket.com.bd/2018/10/29/full-players-list-of-the-teams-following-players-draft-of-bpl-t20-2018-19/ |title=Full players list of the teams following Players Draft of BPL T20 2018\u201319 |work=Bangladesh Cricket Board |accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe [[International Cricket Council]] (ICC) named Khan as one of the five breakout stars in men's cricket in 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icc-cricket.com/news/948077 |title=2018 lookback \u2013 the breakout stars (men) |work=International Cricket Council |accessdate=1 January 2019}}</ref> and in February 2019 he was named in the United States' [[Twenty20 International]] (T20I) squad for their series [[United States cricket team in the United Arab Emirates in 2018\u201319|against the United Arab Emirates]], but did not play due to injury concerns.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/26100265/xavier-marshall-recalled-usa-t20i-tour-uae |title=Xavier Marshall recalled for USA's T20I tour of UAE |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=28 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usacricket.org/team-usa-men/team-usa-squad-announced-for-historic-dubai-tour/ |title=Team USA squad announced for historic Dubai tour |work=USA Cricket |accessdate=28 February 2019}}</ref> The matches were the first T20I fixtures to be played by the United States cricket team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icc-cricket.com/news/1082175 |title=USA name squad for first-ever T20I |work=International Cricket Council |accessdate=28 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2019, he was named in the United States cricket team's squad for the [[2019 ICC World Cricket League Division Two]] tournament in Namibia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icc-cricket.com/media-releases/1173815 |title=All to play for in last ever World Cricket League tournament |work=International Cricket Council |accessdate=11 April 2019}}</ref> In the United States' second match of the tournament, against hosts [[Namibia national cricket team|Namibia]], Khan took his first [[five-wicket haul]] in [[List A cricket]]. He took five wickets for 63 runs from his ten overs, and was named the player of the match.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/1174831.html |title=4th match, ICC World Cricket League Division Two at Windhoek, Apr 21 2019 |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=22 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/26575995/ali-khan-five-turns-namibia-chase-upside-two-run-thriller-usa |title=Ali Khan five-for turns Namibia chase upside down in two-run thriller for USA |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=22 April 2019}}</ref> The United States finished in the top four places in the tournament, therefore gaining [[One Day International]] (ODI) status.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icc-cricket.com/media-releases/1196656 |title=Oman and USA secure ICC Men's Cricket World Cup League 2 places and ODI status |work=International Cricket Council |accessdate=27 April 2019}}</ref> Khan made his ODI debut for the United States on 27 April 2019, against [[Papua New Guinea national cricket team|Papua New Guinea]], in the tournament's third-place playoff.<ref name=\"ODI\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/1174844.html |title=3rd Place Playoff, ICC World Cricket League Division Two at Windhoek, Apr 27 2019 |accessdate=27 April 2019 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref> He was the leading wicket-taker in the tournament, with 17 dismissals in six matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/bowling/most_wickets_career.html?class=5;id=12897;type=tournament |title=ICC World Cricket League Division Two, 2019, List A matches, Most wickets |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=27 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2019, he was named in a 30-man training squad for the [[United States national cricket team|United States cricket team]], ahead of the [[2018\u201319 ICC T20 World Cup Americas Qualifier#Regional Finals|Regional Finals]] of the [[2018\u201319 ICC T20 World Cup Americas Qualifier]] tournament in Bermuda.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/27009108/former-sa-pacer-rusty-theron-named-usa-squad |title=Former SA pacer Rusty Theron named in USA squad |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=19 June 2019}}</ref> Later the same month, he was selected to play for the Vancouver Knights franchise team in the [[2019 Global T20 Canada]] tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.canadacricket.com/?p=12755 |title=Global T20 draft streamed live |work=Canada Cricket Online |accessdate=20 June 2019}}</ref> In August 2019, he was named in the United States' squad for the [[2018\u201319 ICC T20 World Cup Americas Qualifier#Regional Finals|Regional Finals]] of the [[2018\u201319 ICC T20 World Cup Americas Qualifier]] tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usacricket.org/team-usa-men/team-usa-squad-announced-for-icc-t20-world-cup-americas-regional-final/ |title=Team USA Squad Announced for ICC T20 World Cup Americas' Regional Final |work=USA Cricket |accessdate=13 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 March, he debuted for [[Karachi Kings]] against [[Quetta Gladiators]] and conceeded 1/36 in his 3 overs.<ref>https://www.espncricinfo.com/series/8679/scorecard/1211671/karachi-kings-vs-quetta-gladiators-30th-match-pakistan-super-league-2019-20</ref>\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cricinfo|id=927119}}\n\n{{Trinidad and Tobago Red Steel squad}}\n{{Karachi Kings squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Khan, Ali}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American cricketers]]\n[[Category:United States One Day International cricketers]]\n[[Category:Pakistani cricketers]]\n[[Category:Pakistani emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Cricketers from Attock]]\n[[Category:Guyana Amazon Warriors cricketers]]\n[[Category:ICC Americas cricketers]]\n[[Category:Trinbago Knight Riders cricketers]]\n[[Category:Kabul Zwanan cricketers]]\n[[Category:Khulna Titans cricketers]]\n[[Category:Karachi Kings cricketers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|pakistani cricketer}}\n{{distinguish|Mohammad Ali Khan (cricketer)}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox cricketer\n| name = Ali Khan<br/ >{{Nastaliq|\u0639\u0644\u06cc \u062e\u0627\u0646}}\n| image = \n| country = United States\n| fullname = Mohammad Ahsan Ali Khan\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1990|12|13}}\n| birth_place = [[Attock]], [[Punjab, Pakistan]]\n| heightft = \n| heightinch = \n| heightm = \n| batting = Right-handed\n| bowling = Right-arm [[Fast bowling|fast-medium]]\n| role = Bowler\n| international = true\n| internationalspan = 2016\u2013present\n\n|              oneodi = true\n|        odidebutdate = 27 April\n|        odidebutyear = 2019\n|     odidebutagainst = Papua New Guinea\n|              odicap = 15\n|         lastodidate = \n|         lastodiyear = \n|      lastodiagainst =\n\n|             oneT20I = \n|     