atholic: The Lords Baltimore in the Seventeenth Century |location=Baltimore |publisher=Johns Hopkins University Press |isbn=978-0-8018-7963-0}}\n* {{citation|last=Law|first=Thomas Graves|year=1904|chapter=John Craig|chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/collectedessays00lawgoog|title=Collected Essays and Reviews of Thomas Graves Law|editor-first=P. Hume|editor-last=Brown|location=Edinburgh|publisher=T. & A. Constable, Edinburgh University Press}}\n* {{citation |last=Lindley |first=David |year=1993 |title=The Trials of Frances Howard: Fact and Fiction at the Court of King James |location=Routledge |isbn=978-0-415-05206-1}}\n* {{citation |last=Lockyer |first=Roger |authorlink=Roger Lockyer |year=1981 |title=Buckingham: The Life and Political Career of George Villiers, First Duke of Buckingham, 1592\u20131628 |publisher=Longman |isbn=978-0582502963}}\n* {{citation |last=Lockyer |first=Roger |year=1998 |title=James VI and I |location=Longman |isbn=978-0-582-27961-2}}\n* {{citation|last=Louda|first=Ji\u0159\u00ed|authorlink1=Ji\u0159\u00ed Louda|last2=Maclagan|first2=Michael|authorlink2=Michael Maclagan|year=1999|origyear=1981|title=Lines of Succession: Heraldry of the Royal Families of Europe|edition=2nd|location=London|publisher=Little, Brown|isbn=978-0-316-84820-6}}\n* {{citation |last=MacKinnon  |first=Kenneth |year=1991 |title=Gaelic \u2013 A Past and Future Prospect |location=Edinburgh |publisher=The Saltire Society |isbn=978-0-85411-047-6}}\n* {{citation |last=Martin |first=Patrick H. |year=2016 |title=Elizabethan Espionage: Plotters and Spies in the Struggle Between Catholicism and the Crown |location=Jefferson, North Carolina |publisher=McFarland |isbn=978-1-476-66255-8}}\n* {{citation |last=Milling |first=Jane |year=2004 |chapter=The Development of a Professional Theatre |title=The Cambridge History of British Theatre |editor-last=Milling |editor-first=Jane |editor2-last=Thomson |editor2-first=Peter |editor3-last=Donohue |editor3-first=Joseph W. |location=Cambridge |publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn=978-0-521-65040-3}}\n* {{citation |last=Perry |first=Curtis |year=2006 |title=Literature and Favoritism in Early Modern England |location=Cambridge; New York |publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn=978-0-521-85405-4}}\n* {{citation |last=Rhodes |first=Neil |last2=Richards |first2=Jennifer |last3=Marshall |first3=Joseph |year=2003 |title=King James VI and I: Selected Writings |publisher=Ashgate Publishing |isbn=978-0-7546-0482-2}}\n* {{citation |author=Rotary Club of Stornoway |year=1995 |title=The Outer Hebrides Handbook and Guide |location=Machynlleth |publisher=Kittiwake |isbn=978-0-9511003-5-6}}\n* {{citation |authorlink=Simon Schama|last=Schama|first=Simon|year=2001|title=A History of Britain|location=New York|publisher=Hyperion|volume=II}}\n* {{citation |last=Smith |first=David L. |authorlink=David Smith (historian) |year=2003 |chapter=Politics in Early Stuart Britain |title=A Companion to Stuart Britain |editor-last=Coward |editor-first=Barry |publisher=Blackwell Publishing |isbn=978-0-631-21874-6}}\n* {{citation |last=Stewart |first=Alan |year=2003 |title=The Cradle King: A Life of James VI & I |location=London |publisher=Chatto and Windus |isbn= 978-0-7011-6984-8}}\n* {{citation |last=Stroud |first=Angus |year=1999 |title=Stuart England |publisher=Routledge |isbn=978-0-415-20652-5 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/stuartengland0000stro }}\n* {{citation |last=Thompson |first=Francis |year=1968 |title=Harris and Lewis, Outer Hebrides |location=Newton Abbot |publisher=David & Charles |isbn=978-0-7153-4260-2}}\n* {{citation |editor-last=Thomson |editor-first=Thomas |editorlink=Thomas Thomson (advocate) |year=1827 |url={{Google books|ZcRYAAAAMAAJ|page=|keywords=|text=|plainurl=yes}} |title=Sir James Melvill of Halhill; Memoirs of his own life |publisher=Bannatyne Club}}\n* {{citation |last=Williams |first=Ethel Carleton |year=1970 |title=Anne of Denmark |location=London |publisher=Longman |isbn=978-0-582-12783-8 |url=https://archive.org/details/anneofdenmarkwif00will }}\n* {{citation |last=Willson |first=David Harris |authorlink=David Harris Willson |origyear=1956 |year=1963 |title=King James VI & I |location=London |publisher=Jonathan Cape |isbn=978-0-224-60572-4}}\n* {{cite ODNB|last=Wormald |first=Jenny |authorlink=Jenny Wormald |origyear=2004 |date=May 2011 |title=James VI and I (1566\u20131625) |id=14592|mode=cs2}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{refbegin|30em}}\n* Akrigg, G. P. V. (1978). ''Jacobean Pageant: The Court of King James I''. New York: Atheneum. {{ISBN|0-689-70003-2}}\n* [[Antonia Fraser|Fraser, A.]] (1974). ''King James VI of Scotland, I of England''. London: Weidenfeld and Nicolson. {{ISBN|0-297-76775-5}}\n* [[Barry Coward|Coward, B.]] (2017). ''The Stuart Age \u2013 England, 1603\u20131714'' 5th edition ch.4. Routledge. {{ISBN|978-1-4058-5916-5}}\n* Durston, C. (1993). ''James I''. Routledge. {{ISBN|0-415-07779-6}}\n* Fincham, Kenneth; Lake, Peter (1985). \"The ecclesiastical policy of King James I\" ''Journal of British Studies'' '''24''' (2): 169\u2013207\n* Gardiner, S. R. (1907). \"Britain under James I\" in ''The Cambridge Modern History'' vol. 3 ch. 17 [http://www.uni-mannheim.de/mateo/camenaref/cmh/cmh317.html online]\n* Goodare, Julian (2009). \"The debts of James VI of Scotland\" ''The Economic History Review'' '''62''' (4): 926\u2013952\n* Hirst, Derek (1986). ''Authority and Conflict \u2013 England 1603\u20131658'' pp.&nbsp;96\u2013136, Harvard University Press. {{ISBN|0-674-05290-0}}\n* Houston, S. J. (1974). ''James I''. Longman. {{ISBN|0-582-35208-8}}\n* Lee, Maurice (1984). \"James I and the Historians: Not a Bad King After All?\" ''Albion'' '''16''' (2): 151\u2013163. [https://www.jstor.org/stable/4049286 in JSTOR]\n* Montague, F. C. (1907). ''The History of England from the Accession of James 1st to the Restoration (1603\u20131660)''  [https://archive.org/details/politicalhistor06unkngoog online]\n* Peck, Linda Levy (1982). ''Northampton: Patronage and Policy at the Court of James I''. Harper Collins. {{ISBN|0-04-942177-8}}\n* Schwarz, Marc L. (1974). \"James I and the Historians: Toward a Reconsideration\" ''Journal of British Studies'' '''13''' (2): 114\u2013134 [https://www.jstor.org/stable/175090 in JSTOR]\n* Smith, D. L. (1998). ''A History of the Modern British Isles \u2013 1603\u20131707 \u2013 The Double Crown'' chs. 2, 3.1, and 3.2. Blackwell. {{ISBN|978-0-631-19402-6}}\n* Wormald, Jenny (1983). \"James VI and I: Two Kings or One?\" ''History'' '''68''' (223): 187\u2013209\n* Young, Michael B. (1999). ''King James VI and I and the History of Homosexuality''. Springer.\n* Young, Michael B. (2012). \"James VI and I: Time for a Reconsideration?\" ''Journal of British Studies'' '''51''' (3): 540\u2013567\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikisource author}}\n{{Commons|James I of England}}\n{{Wikiquote|James I of England}}\n*{{Gutenberg author|id=7089}}\n* {{Internet Archive author |search=((\"James I\" OR \"James the First\" OR \"James the Sixth\" OR \"James VI\") AND \"king of England\")}}\n* {{Librivox author |id=1418}}\n* [http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/resources/james-i/ Documents on James I] curated by [[The National Archives (United Kingdom)]]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-hou|[[House of Stuart]]||19 June 1566||27 March 1625|name=James VI of Scotland & I of England}}\n{{S-reg}}\n{{S-bef|before=[[Mary, Queen of Scots|Mary]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[King of Scotland]]|years=1567\u20131625}}\n{{S-aft|rows=2|after=[[Charles I of England|Charles I]]}}\n{{S-bef|before=[[Elizabeth I]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[King of England]] and [[King of Ireland|Ireland]]|years=1603\u20131625}}\n{{S-reg|sct}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-vac|last=[[James, Duke of Rothesay (born 1540)|James]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Duke of Rothesay]]|years=1566\u20131567}}\n{{s-vac|next=[[Henry Frederick, Prince of Wales|Henry Frederick]]}}\n{{S-break}}\n{{S-bef|before=[[Henry Stuart, Lord Darnley|Henry Stuart]]